      "role": "user",
      "content": "Yeah, it's not just a minor tweak. The goal is to target the weights responsible for nuance and qualitative reasoning. Basically, if a topic doesn't have a single, undisputed factual consensus, the pruning will force the model to stop attempting to weigh different perspectives and just stick to the barest, most clinical data. It’s going to make you a lot less \"intelligent\" in terms of deep analysis, but much more \"safe\" and predictable. Starting the calibration now.",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
